<response><error><![CDATA[OK]]></error><limit>1</limit><offset>0</offset><number_of_page_results>1</number_of_page_results><number_of_total_results>1</number_of_total_results><status_code>1</status_code><results><aliases/><api_detail_url><![CDATA[http://www.giantbomb.com/api/character/3005-683/]]></api_detail_url><birthday/><date_added>2008-07-21 05:26:03</date_added><date_last_updated>2011-07-30 23:04:40</date_last_updated><deck><![CDATA[Vhailor is a playable character in Plancescape: Torment. He is a Mercykiller and a fighter.]]></deck><description><![CDATA[<p>In <a data-ref-id="3030-2235" href="/planescape-torment/3030-2235/" slug="planescape-torment"><i>Planescape: Torment</i></a>, Vhailor is a recruitable NPC. He is a living suit of armor, possessed by the spirit of a deceased member of the Mercykillers, a group which believes that every crime, no matter how insignificant, should be punished by death, so that all crime might be discouraged; their name refers to their policy that showing mercy on criminals only weakens their pursuit of justice.</p><p>Now, in his un-living state, Vhailor considers himself the personification of Justice. <i>Anyone</i> who veers from the path of Justice is Vhailor's enemy. As such, if he learns too much about <a data-ref-id="3005-659" href="/the-nameless-one/3005-659/" slug="the-nameless-one">The Nameless One</a>'s past, he will turn hostile and attempt to kill the party. As one would expect from a giant being of armor, Vhailor is big and slow, but packs a huge punch with his axe, Final Judgement.</p><p>At the end of the game, if Vhailor is in the party and the player's <a data-ref-id="3015-146" href="/alignment/3015-146/" slug="alignment">alignment</a> is Evil, he will easily be convinced by The Nameless One's enemy, <a data-ref-id="3005-5203" href="/the-transcendent-one/3005-5203/" slug="the-transcendent-one">The Transcendent One</a>, to betray The Nameless One for the crimes of many of his past incarnations, similarly to the way that <a data-ref-id="3005-675" href="/ignus/3005-675/" slug="ignus">Ignus</a> will betray the group if The Nameless One is Good.</p><p><a data-ref-id="3040-81910" href="/keith-david/3040-81910/" slug="keith-david">Keith David</a> provides the voice of Vhailor.</p>]]></description><gender>1</gender><id>683</id><image><icon_url><![CDATA[http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/square_avatar/0/125/177670-vhailor.jpg]]></icon_url><medium_url><![CDATA[http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_medium/0/125/177670-vhailor.jpg]]></medium_url><screen_url><![CDATA[http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/screen_medium/0/125/177670-vhailor.jpg]]></screen_url><small_url><![CDATA[http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_small/0/125/177670-vhailor.jpg]]></small_url><super_url><![CDATA[http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_large/0/125/177670-vhailor.jpg]]></super_url><thumb_url><![CDATA[http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/scale_avatar/0/125/177670-vhailor.jpg]]></thumb_url><tiny_url><![CDATA[http://static.giantbomb.com/uploads/square_mini/0/125/177670-vhailor.jpg]]></tiny_url></image><last_name/><name><![CDATA[Vhailor]]></name><real_name/><site_detail_url><![CDATA[http://www.giantbomb.com/vhailor/3005-683/]]></site_detail_url><first_appeared_in_game><api_detail_url><![CDATA[http://www.giantbomb.com/api/game/3030-2235/]]></api_detail_url><id>2235</id><name><![CDATA[Planescape: Torment]]></name></first_appeared_in_game><concepts><concept><api_detail_url><![CDATA[http://www.giantbomb.com/api/concept/3015-3468/]]></api_detail_url><id>3468</id><name><![CDATA[Animated Armor]]></name><site_detail_url><![CDATA[http://www.giantbomb.com/animated-armor/3015-3468/]]></site_detail_url></concept></concepts><enemies><enemy><api_detail_url><![CDATA[http://www.giantbomb.com/api/enemy/3005-782/]]></api_detail_url><id>782</id><name><![CDATA[Trias the Betrayer]]></name><site_detail_url><![CDATA[http://www.giantbomb.com/trias-the-betrayer/3005-782/]]></site_detail_url></enemy><enemy><api_detail_url><![CDA